    "raw_text": "Assistance with Hardships\nFinancial Hardship Related Programs and Ideas\nState Rep. Martina White\nFood Assistance\n• Philadelphia City Government Sponsored Food Banks List\nhttps://www.phila.gov/food/#/\n•\tArea Food Banks and Food Assistance Services:\no\tSomerton Food Bank - 510 Somerton Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19116 9:30am- 12pm on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday (215-673-1117)\no\tHoly Redeemer Food Cupboard - 12265 Townsend Rd Philadelphia, PA 19154 Call for availability: 215-856-1370\no\tFeast of Justice - 3101 Tyson Ave, Philadelphia, PA 19149, Sackett St Entrance, by appointment only: 215-268-3510\no\tHarvest Ministry - 2284 Bristol Pk, Bensalem, PA 19020 Call for availability: (215) 639-0436\nFederal Resources Available:\n•\tFederal Government Assistance Website\nhttps://www.usa.gov/benefit-finder\nUtilities/Home Services Help\n•\tGreater Philadelphia Community Alliance (215-336-5505)\nhttps://www.gpca-phila.org/\n•\tPhiladelphia Housing Development Corporation (PHDC) Home Repair Programs (215-448-3000)\nhttps://phdcphila.org/\n•\tOne Philly Front Door\nhttps://housing-front-door.phila.gov/\n•\tUtility Emergency Services Fund (UESF) Utility Grants (215-972-5170)\nhttps://uesfacts.org/our-programs/utility-grant-program/\n•\tPECO CAP (1-800-774-7040)\nhttps://secure.peco.com/CapAssistance/CAPRateApplication\no\tUnited Way: PECO Customer Relief Fund 2025\nhttps://unitedforimpact.org/\n•\tPGW Cares, Customer Responsibility Program, & Senior Citizen Discount  (215-235-1000)\nhttps://www.pgworks.com/customer-care/payment-assistance\n•\tPhila Water Department: Senior Citizen Discount and the Tiered Assistance Program (TAP) (215) 685-6300\nhttps://cap.phila.gov/\nHousing Resources:\n•\tPA Housing Finance Agency -\nhttps://www.phfa.org/pacares/rent.aspx\n•\tRental Legal Assistance:\no\tPhiladelphia Eviction Prevention Project - (267-443-2500)\nhttps://www.phillytenant.org/\no\tPA Attorney General’s Consumer Hotline – (1-800-441-2555 Main /215-560-2414